 use earplugs.I didn’t test out the breakfast that was included as I prefer a full English breakfast rather than a continental one, which was the only option this hotel offered. However, I would strongly recommend the less than £5 English breakfast at the local pub the Stanhope Arms, which was perfectly cooked and really good value. All in all, I spent two better-than-expected nights at this apartment hotel in London. Great location close to Gloucester Road tube station, clean appearance, huge bed and fairly good service makes this hotel one of the better accommodation options in central London. I would definitely recommend it to others, but the next time I visit London on my own, I would probably find a hotel with smaller rooms that serves English breakfast ;)	
