Jan 24 2008 	Good-- as long as you're never in the room	I am currently staying in Fraser Place for an extended corporate stay and I would highly discourage anyone from staying here for more than one week, or for using the room as anything more than a sleeping/showering location. Like previous reviewers noted, the kitchen is lacking any kind of actual cooking apparatus, so, other than sandwiches and cereal, we eat out for most of our meals. The service here is spotty; sometimes the front desk is helpful, but they frequently do not answer the phone or provide accurate help. Like a previous reviewer, I too have had plumbing problems, as well as the heating/air conditioning unit making extreme noises. Finally, the apartment is barely cleaned. When we arrived, there was a half-used shampoo bottle laid out for our use and the toilet looked like it could use a thorough cleaning. I have reached out to the management several times about the deficiencies of the room and have received some help at times, and no help at other times. If you are here with a family to tour London, and you plan on not being in the apartment much, I am sure this is a fine place for you to stay. But if you are looking for an extended stay apartment-type situation, keep on looking...	
Nov 25 2007 	Not Bad for London	We took a chance on the Fraser Place Queen's Gate as we wanted a larger room (traveling with our two sons) and a price that was good for London. Overall, the hotel delivered for us.The room had recenly been renovated and everything was in good shape and clean. We had a bedroom, large bathroom and a combined living/kitchen area with a hide-a-bed. The bed in the bedroom was nice and large, but our boys were a little close in the other bed. Our room was quiet as we were away from Cromwell (and we were not in the basement). Heat worked okay and it did appear to have air conditioning (not an issue for us). We noticed some odd smells in the hall, but had no problem in our room.Service was &quot;okay&quot;. When checking in, it felt as if we were disturbing the clerk. She was also less than friendly when we had to call several times to request bedding for the fold-out bed. On the plus side, the cleaning was great and they were able to arrange a car to the airport (once someone finally picked up the phone). Price was lower than we could find elsewhere (booked via hotel website).Location was good as we were less than two blocks from the Natural History Museum and the Gloucester Tube stop. There were three grocery stores nearby, so we were able to make use of our kitchen and save money at breakfast. The South Kensington area seemed more touristy than other areas of the city we've stayed in, but it is convenient especially with the tube.	
