Jul 21 2007 	Great location but not fully reburbished	A family of 4 (including a toddler and a teen) stayed in a 1 BR apartment here, with small kitchen facilities, modern furniture, comfortable bed. The location is great, close to museums, parks, shops and the tube. This property was recently sold and is still being refurbished (there was scaffolding and green mesh covering most of the hotel's exterior), though their website does not mention that and nor did the staff member I communicated with when booking. Our apartment was light, spatious, but suffered from various problemsthat were all relatively small but added up: the phone didn't work, akitchen cabinet door was coming unhinged and almost fell off, no towel rack, no bedding for sofa bed, etc. Staff were not entirely professional nor did they seem very interested in us or our staying here. This is more of an apartment building than a hotel, but for the price (169 pounds/night in summer peak season), location, lots of space for a family, and the ability to stay only 4 nights, it suited us well.	
